io.smudgr.app.project.util

Class IdProvider

  • java.lang.Object
    • io.smudgr.app.project.util.IdProvider

  • public class IdProvider
extends java.lang.Object
    Tracks ProjectItem items for the project by managing a ProjectItem map paired with unique integer IDs.

      • add

        public void add(ProjectItem item)
        Add a ProjectItem to the ID map with a new unique ID.

        If the item has an ID, it has already been added, and this method does nothing.

        Parameters:
        item - ProjectItem to add
        See Also:
        Project.add(ProjectItem)

      • put

        public void put(ProjectItem item,
                int id)
        Put a ProjectItem at the given ID in the ID map.

        If the item has already been added at the given ID, this method does nothing.

        If another item exists at the given ID, this method prints an error and does nothing.

        If the item exists at a different ID and the given ID is available, this method removes the old ID reference and then puts them item at the given ID.

        Parameters:
        item - ProjectItem
        id - int Positive unique ID.
        See Also:
        Project.put(ProjectItem, int)

      • remove

        public void remove(ProjectItem item)
        Remove a ProjectItem item from the ID map. The old item ID is made available for use again.
        Parameters:
        item - ProjectItem
        See Also:
        Project.remove(ProjectItem)
